1
00:01:47,920 --> 00:01:49,870
In the mid-1990s,

2
00:01:50,640 --> 00:01:52,560
in the Uninhabited Zone of Mazhi County

3
00:01:52,560 --> 00:01:54,690
in the southwest of Qinghai Province,

4
00:01:55,150 --> 00:01:56,500
cases of Tibetan antelope poaching

5
00:01:56,500 --> 00:01:59,160
and illegal mineral extraction were frequent.

6
00:02:00,140 --> 00:02:01,640
The region was vast

7
00:02:02,290 --> 00:02:04,090
and police forces were limited,

8
00:02:04,450 --> 00:02:07,090
so the Mazhi County Party Committee and county government

9
00:02:07,090 --> 00:02:09,090
decided to form an armed patrol unit

10
00:02:09,650 --> 00:02:11,800
led by Deputy County Mayor Duojie,

11
00:02:11,930 --> 00:02:13,800
made up of personnel from Mazhi Economic Development Company

12
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:15,300
and local militia.

13
00:02:16,780 --> 00:02:17,440
At the time,

14
00:02:18,280 --> 00:02:20,500
I had just graduated from the police academy

15
00:02:20,500 --> 00:02:22,650
and was seconded to the Mountain Patrol,

16
00:02:22,650 --> 00:02:24,400
responsible for supervising law enforcement

17
00:02:24,400 --> 00:02:26,000
and transferring suspects.

18
00:02:26,870 --> 00:02:27,690
Back then,

19
00:02:28,250 --> 00:02:29,500
I had no idea what this reassignment

20
00:02:29,500 --> 00:02:30,560
would come to mean.

21
00:02:31,840 --> 00:02:33,100
That was the first time

22
00:02:33,740 --> 00:02:35,130
I learned of the place that would be

23
00:02:35,130 --> 00:02:37,210
in my dreams for the rest of my life—

24
00:02:38,470 --> 00:02:39,630
Bolamula.

25
00:03:15,150 --> 00:03:15,970
Drive steadily!

26
00:03:15,970 --> 00:03:17,430
Aim carefully!

27
00:03:24,870 --> 00:03:25,900
Shoot the tires!

28
00:03:26,150 --> 00:03:27,079
Shoot the tires!

29
00:03:27,240 --> 00:03:28,180
You do it!

30
00:03:31,810 --> 00:03:32,540
Stop the car!

31
00:04:04,810 --> 00:04:05,310
Dongzhiba!

32
00:04:05,310 --> 00:04:05,970
Here! Guns!

33
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:06,810
Jiu Mei, get down!

34
00:04:06,810 --> 00:04:07,140
Okay!

35
00:04:07,750 --> 00:04:08,750
Zhacuo, bullets!

36
00:04:15,780 --> 00:04:16,930
Two for me, one for you!

37
00:04:16,930 --> 00:04:17,990
Give them all to me!

38
00:04:18,540 --> 00:04:19,450
You can't shoot straight,

39
00:04:19,450 --> 00:04:21,050
but you use the most bullets!

40
00:04:25,240 --> 00:04:26,240
Are you guys okay?

41
00:04:26,480 --> 00:04:27,130
I'm fine!

42
00:04:34,540 --> 00:04:34,890
Han!

43
00:04:37,950 --> 00:04:39,310
I'm fine! I'm fine!

44
00:04:40,830 --> 00:04:41,630
Any bullets left?

45
00:04:41,630 --> 00:04:42,220
None.

46
00:04:45,659 --> 00:04:46,920
I'm out of bullets too.

47
00:05:28,660 --> 00:05:29,190
Alright!

48
00:05:29,830 --> 00:05:30,360
Let's go!

49
00:06:03,660 --> 00:06:04,560
Bastards!

50
00:06:50,890 --> 00:06:52,220
Should we keep chasing?

51
00:06:53,890 --> 00:06:55,680
We’ve only got two days of fuel left.

52
00:06:55,680 --> 00:06:57,140
Barely enough to get back.

53
00:08:01,740 --> 00:08:03,660
You greedy little thing.

54
00:08:04,100 --> 00:08:05,310
How did you get here?

55
00:08:07,510 --> 00:08:08,840
Don't move. Don't move.

56
00:08:09,370 --> 00:08:10,510
Your leg is caught, isn’t it?

57
00:08:10,510 --> 00:08:11,170
Don't move.

58
00:08:15,310 --> 00:08:15,950
There.

59
00:08:18,240 --> 00:08:19,300
Alright, alright.

60
00:08:19,480 --> 00:08:20,240
I'll take you back

61
00:08:20,240 --> 00:08:21,560
to Grandma.

62
00:08:23,630 --> 00:08:25,390
If you run off again,

63
00:08:25,890 --> 00:08:27,680
a wolf might eat you.

64
00:08:54,840 --> 00:08:55,790
No, no.

65
00:08:56,600 --> 00:08:57,730
This isn't my sheep.

66
00:08:57,960 --> 00:08:58,870
Take it back.

67
00:09:02,480 --> 00:09:03,390
It's not your sheep?

68
00:09:03,390 --> 00:09:05,150
But it has black hair on its head.

69
00:09:05,150 --> 00:09:06,390
Not black hair in the middle.

70
00:09:06,390 --> 00:09:08,370
My sheep has black hair on both ears.

71
00:09:08,370 --> 00:09:10,230
Go look again. Take this one back.

72
00:09:10,890 --> 00:09:11,600
Ma'am.

73
00:09:12,650 --> 00:09:13,780
What about this one?

74
00:09:14,340 --> 00:09:15,500
Take it back.

75
00:09:16,480 --> 00:09:17,250
Ma'am.

76
00:09:17,620 --> 00:09:19,000
Where should I take it back?

77
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:20,860
Tudan's car is running out of gas.

78
00:09:21,030 --> 00:09:22,160
Have some tea first.

79
00:09:25,010 --> 00:09:26,540
Miss, please have some tea.

80
00:09:26,860 --> 00:09:27,740
Thank you.

81
00:09:31,340 --> 00:09:32,550
After you finish your tea,

82
00:09:32,550 --> 00:09:33,880
go find the sheep for me.

83
00:09:34,500 --> 00:09:35,890
Where should I go?

84
00:09:38,250 --> 00:09:39,290
In the mountains.

85
00:09:39,600 --> 00:09:40,500
You'll find it.

86
00:09:57,080 --> 00:09:57,810
You're back?

87
00:09:58,320 --> 00:09:58,890
Yes.

88
00:10:01,440 --> 00:10:02,040
Sister.【】

89
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:03,930
You're back?

90
00:10:07,050 --> 00:10:08,310
Who gave you the sheep?

91
00:10:08,360 --> 00:10:11,420
I was helping someone find a sheep but got the wrong one.

92
00:10:12,050 --> 00:10:13,450
How did you cut your face?

93
00:10:13,820 --> 00:10:14,750
I don't know how I got it.

94
00:10:14,750 --> 00:10:15,460
It's fine. It doesn't hurt.

95
00:10:15,460 --> 00:10:16,390
It doesn't hurt?

96
00:10:16,530 --> 00:10:17,550
I'll go put the gun away first.

97
00:10:17,550 --> 00:10:17,880
Okay.

98
00:10:17,980 --> 00:10:19,440
I'll look for its owner later.

99
00:10:19,440 --> 00:10:19,770
Okay.

100
00:10:21,700 --> 00:10:22,620
Here. Let me.

101
00:10:23,750 --> 00:10:24,650
We're all back.

102
00:10:24,750 --> 00:10:26,480
Go back and get some rest.

103
00:10:26,870 --> 00:10:27,960
Rest?

104
00:10:28,050 --> 00:10:30,120
I’ve been doing nothing for over 10 days.

105
00:10:30,120 --> 00:10:32,380
Save your energy for writing the report.

106
00:10:32,410 --> 00:10:34,340
Using your brain can be tiring too.

107
00:10:34,480 --> 00:10:36,290
This time we were out for 12 days.

108
00:10:37,650 --> 00:10:38,740
We caught 15 people

109
00:10:39,370 --> 00:10:40,620
and released 13.

110
00:10:41,120 --> 00:10:42,050
Write it all down

111
00:10:42,820 --> 00:10:43,820
so the higher-ups

112
00:10:43,840 --> 00:10:45,240
will show us some concern.

113
00:10:45,240 --> 00:10:46,480
I even beat up two guys

114
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:47,800
and took their

115
00:10:47,820 --> 00:10:49,030
gasoline and steamed buns.

116
00:10:49,030 --> 00:10:50,760
Write it all down, Officer Bai.

117
00:10:54,120 --> 00:10:54,910
The lazy donkey

118
00:10:54,910 --> 00:10:56,370
always brays the loudest.

119
00:10:56,720 --> 00:10:57,450
Ignore them.

120
00:10:59,080 --> 00:10:59,940
Bai, come here.

121
00:11:04,340 --> 00:11:05,470
These two are yours.

122
00:11:07,770 --> 00:11:08,630
Skinners?

123
00:11:09,510 --> 00:11:11,110
Did you catch them in the act?

124
00:11:11,510 --> 00:11:12,250
On our way back,

125
00:11:12,250 --> 00:11:13,460
passing Zhuoyuan Lake,

126
00:11:13,460 --> 00:11:15,770
we saw them digging holes to bury the pelts.

127
00:11:15,770 --> 00:11:17,460
They’ve already paid the fine.

128
00:11:17,460 --> 00:11:17,910
Take them

129
00:11:17,910 --> 00:11:19,970
to the Public Security Bureau later.

130
00:11:20,010 --> 00:11:22,200
So you didn’t catch any gunmen this time either?

131
00:11:22,200 --> 00:11:23,130
If a gunman is caught,

132
00:11:23,130 --> 00:11:24,190
he gets sentenced.

133
00:11:25,130 --> 00:11:26,120
These people are very sly.

134
00:11:26,120 --> 00:11:27,510
They had run off long ago.

135
00:11:27,510 --> 00:11:28,050
Officer,

136
00:11:28,340 --> 00:11:29,250
please give us some water.

137
00:11:29,250 --> 00:11:30,310
Give us some water.

138
00:11:30,360 --> 00:11:31,000
Give us some water.

139
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:31,650
Got it.

140
00:11:32,470 --> 00:11:33,910
You two have been whining the whole way back.

141
00:11:33,910 --> 00:11:34,320
Here.

142
00:11:35,010 --> 00:11:35,620
Take this.

143
00:11:37,370 --> 00:11:39,370
Why did you wash the door curtain?

144
00:11:40,130 --> 00:11:41,170
It was filthy.

145
00:11:41,510 --> 00:11:43,110
Of course it needed washing.

146
00:11:46,340 --> 00:11:47,220
Bai.

147
00:11:48,910 --> 00:11:50,120
Where is my quilt?

148
00:11:50,480 --> 00:11:50,870
That quilt of yours

149
00:11:50,870 --> 00:11:52,290
was almost stiff as a rock.

150
00:11:52,290 --> 00:11:53,750
I took it to get fluffed up.

151
00:11:54,050 --> 00:11:56,240
Then what am I supposed to sleep with tonight?

152
00:11:56,240 --> 00:11:56,980
This.

153
00:11:58,340 --> 00:11:59,940
Go ask Mrs. Nima yourself.

154
00:12:02,530 --> 00:12:04,530
How am I supposed to sleep with this?

155
00:12:05,720 --> 00:12:06,290
Bai!

156
00:12:08,740 --> 00:12:09,270
Bai!

157
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:10,440
Bai!

158
00:12:13,360 --> 00:12:14,000
Look.

159
00:12:14,600 --> 00:12:15,530
From this page

160
00:12:15,620 --> 00:12:16,550
to the end

161
00:12:17,030 --> 00:12:18,630
is the record of this patrol.

162
00:12:18,670 --> 00:12:20,530
Take it and use it for your report.

163
00:12:21,890 --> 00:12:23,170
I kept it pretty...

164
00:12:23,270 --> 00:12:24,030
pretty detailed.

165
00:12:24,030 --> 00:12:24,410
Just don’t

166
00:12:24,410 --> 00:12:25,700
write everything in there.

167
00:12:25,700 --> 00:12:26,120
Here.

168
00:12:27,840 --> 00:12:28,900
I'm not writing it.

169
00:12:30,360 --> 00:12:30,960
Sangba and Zhacuo

170
00:12:30,960 --> 00:12:32,290
were not targeting you.

171
00:12:32,630 --> 00:12:34,320
They just don't like being controlled.

172
00:12:34,320 --> 00:12:34,980
When I tried

173
00:12:34,980 --> 00:12:36,000
to discipline them in the mountains,

174
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:37,580
they cursed me even worse.

175
00:12:38,340 --> 00:12:39,870
I know what they're like.

176
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:40,820
I'm used to it.

177
00:12:41,910 --> 00:12:43,310
It's not because of that.

178
00:12:45,550 --> 00:12:47,150
I’m being transferred back.

179
00:12:49,820 --> 00:12:50,620
Is it decided?

180
00:12:52,630 --> 00:12:53,100
Bye.

181
00:12:59,290 --> 00:12:59,890
Come back.

182
00:13:00,240 --> 00:13:01,440
Where is the Captain?

183
00:13:38,220 --> 00:13:39,240
What's going on?

184
00:13:42,840 --> 00:13:43,620
Deputy County Mayor Duo,

185
00:13:43,620 --> 00:13:44,950
what are you doing here?

186
00:13:47,220 --> 00:13:47,650
Deputy County Mayor Duo,

187
00:13:47,650 --> 00:13:48,290
this door is broken.

188
00:13:48,290 --> 00:13:50,350
You have to get in from the other side.

189
00:14:01,080 --> 00:14:03,080
Who are you showing this poverty to?

190
00:14:03,320 --> 00:14:04,010
To you.

191
00:14:10,960 --> 00:14:11,910
Deputy County Mayor Duo,

192
00:14:11,910 --> 00:14:13,370
where should I take you to?

193
00:14:14,290 --> 00:14:15,090
To the county.

194
00:14:15,700 --> 00:14:16,630
To get the money.

195
00:14:20,890 --> 00:14:21,420
Let's go.

196
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:27,670
Lin,

197
00:14:28,010 --> 00:14:28,750
we agreed a long time ago

198
00:14:28,750 --> 00:14:29,480
that the 30,000

199
00:14:29,480 --> 00:14:31,080
can't be delayed any longer.

200
00:14:31,440 --> 00:14:32,110
The team hasn’t been paid

201
00:14:32,110 --> 00:14:33,220
for 3 months.

202
00:14:33,510 --> 00:14:35,550
We’ve been putting off paying for the fuel.

203
00:14:35,550 --> 00:14:36,650
Now we can barely afford

204
00:14:36,650 --> 00:14:37,580
to feed the men.

205
00:14:38,600 --> 00:14:39,870
Relying on fines to plug the hole

206
00:14:39,870 --> 00:14:41,130
is not enough anymore.

207
00:14:49,130 --> 00:14:51,010
The funding requests we submitted to the city

208
00:14:51,010 --> 00:14:51,820
are all here.

209
00:14:52,200 --> 00:14:54,010
Yours is in there too. Not approved.

210
00:14:54,010 --> 00:14:54,860
Only one disaster relief request

211
00:14:54,860 --> 00:14:55,660
got approved.

212
00:14:56,010 --> 00:14:56,770
Do you want that money?

213
00:14:56,770 --> 00:14:57,960
Don’t play this game with me.

214
00:14:57,960 --> 00:14:59,170
The Mountain Patrol's funding

215
00:14:59,170 --> 00:14:59,820
was promised

216
00:14:59,820 --> 00:15:00,630
3 months ago.

217
00:15:01,030 --> 00:15:02,250
It was a collective decision by the county.

218
00:15:02,250 --> 00:15:03,910
You can't go back on your word.

219
00:15:04,510 --> 00:15:05,910
If you're going to talk to me like that,

220
00:15:05,910 --> 00:15:06,460
we’ll have to

221
00:15:06,460 --> 00:15:07,630
sort this out properly.

222
00:15:07,630 --> 00:15:08,290
Who was it

223
00:15:08,410 --> 00:15:10,340
that went back on their word first?

224
00:15:11,410 --> 00:15:12,480
Why was the establishment

225
00:15:12,480 --> 00:15:14,170
of the Mountain Patrol approved in the first place?

226
00:15:14,170 --> 00:15:14,700
Why?

227
00:15:15,170 --> 00:15:15,910
On the official seal given to you,

228
00:15:15,910 --> 00:15:16,700
what does it say?

229
00:15:16,700 --> 00:15:19,230
Mazhi County Economic Development Company!

230
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:21,670
You made this pledge yourself—

231
00:15:21,670 --> 00:15:22,100
in the first year,

232
00:15:22,100 --> 00:15:23,240
the development company would be established;

233
00:15:23,240 --> 00:15:23,790
in the second year,

234
00:15:23,790 --> 00:15:24,790
it would be weaned off county funding

235
00:15:24,790 --> 00:15:25,600
and become self-sustaining;

236
00:15:25,600 --> 00:15:26,270
in the third year,

237
00:15:26,270 --> 00:15:27,940
it would start contributing to the county’s finances.

238
00:15:27,940 --> 00:15:29,080
Do those promises still count?

239
00:15:29,080 --> 00:15:29,840
I’m asking you,

240
00:15:29,840 --> 00:15:31,050
do they still count?

241
00:15:31,150 --> 00:15:32,600
Poaching in the mountains

242
00:15:32,600 --> 00:15:33,460
is rampant now.

243
00:15:33,460 --> 00:15:33,890
If Tibetan antelopes

244
00:15:33,890 --> 00:15:34,790
keep getting killed like this,

245
00:15:34,790 --> 00:15:35,920
they’ll go extinct.

246
00:15:35,940 --> 00:15:36,460
Are we just supposed to stand by

247
00:15:36,460 --> 00:15:37,200
and do nothing?

248
00:15:37,200 --> 00:15:37,890
Then what about development?

249
00:15:37,890 --> 00:15:39,090
Are we doing it or not?

250
00:15:40,010 --> 00:15:40,370
Yes.

251
00:15:40,460 --> 00:15:40,990
Alright.

252
00:15:41,050 --> 00:15:41,440
You need to do it

253
00:15:41,440 --> 00:15:42,970
on the basis of protection.

254
00:15:47,860 --> 00:15:48,480
Last year,

255
00:15:49,390 --> 00:15:51,530
county revenue was 2 million,

256
00:15:51,840 --> 00:15:53,640
and expenditure was 10 million.

257
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:55,930
I can’t account for that at all.

258
00:15:56,870 --> 00:15:57,890
This time when I went to the city,

259
00:15:57,890 --> 00:15:59,700
not only did I fail to get any money,

260
00:15:59,700 --> 00:16:00,840
but the city leaders also brought up

261
00:16:00,840 --> 00:16:02,300
the animal husbandry tax.

262
00:16:03,750 --> 00:16:04,630
Didn’t this year’s proposal
to the National People’s Congress

263
00:16:04,630 --> 00:16:05,910
request a reduction?

264
00:16:06,010 --> 00:16:07,240
It did,

265
00:16:07,340 --> 00:16:09,670
but it’s still going through the process.

266
00:16:13,700 --> 00:16:16,360
Then what about the Mountain Patrol’s funding?

267
00:16:22,390 --> 00:16:24,120
I don’t like the smell of smoke.

268
00:16:28,150 --> 00:16:28,880
Stop the car!

269
00:16:50,700 --> 00:16:52,100
Deputy County Mayor Duo!

270
00:16:54,200 --> 00:16:55,600
Deputy County Mayor Duo!

271
00:17:00,290 --> 00:17:01,690
Deputy County Mayor Duo!

272
00:17:03,120 --> 00:17:04,500
Is the County Mayor looking for me?

273
00:17:04,500 --> 00:17:05,200
No.

274
00:17:05,270 --> 00:17:06,220
Deputy County Mayor Duo,

275
00:17:06,220 --> 00:17:07,280
the car broke down.

276
00:17:07,329 --> 00:17:08,589
Could you help push it?

277
00:17:14,720 --> 00:17:15,349
Here.

278
00:17:24,740 --> 00:17:25,550
Just two people?

279
00:17:25,550 --> 00:17:26,329
No pelts?

280
00:17:27,050 --> 00:17:27,500
In a couple of days,

281
00:17:27,500 --> 00:17:28,830
they'll send them over.

282
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:30,160
They haven't finished counting yet.

283
00:17:30,160 --> 00:17:30,960
Alright then.

284
00:17:31,270 --> 00:17:32,200
It's like this every time—

285
00:17:32,200 --> 00:17:33,460
handing over people but not the pelts.

286
00:17:33,460 --> 00:17:34,400
But don't they always

287
00:17:34,400 --> 00:17:35,860
send them to you in the end?

288
00:17:36,420 --> 00:17:38,290
The point is they need to be aired out,

289
00:17:38,290 --> 00:17:39,620
and rotten ones burned.

290
00:17:40,000 --> 00:17:41,290
We can bring them now if you want.

291
00:17:41,290 --> 00:17:42,220
We'll just pile them all here.

292
00:17:42,220 --> 00:17:42,940
As long as you don't mind the stink.

293
00:17:42,940 --> 00:17:43,510
There are hundreds.

294
00:17:43,510 --> 00:17:44,440
Do you want them?

295
00:17:46,110 --> 00:17:46,850
Forget it.

296
00:17:47,810 --> 00:17:48,670
The problem is,

297
00:17:49,270 --> 00:17:50,800
you brought these two over,

298
00:17:51,010 --> 00:17:52,110
but no pelts.

299
00:17:52,610 --> 00:17:54,050
We can’t interrogate them,

300
00:17:54,050 --> 00:17:56,310
and we still have to feed them.

301
00:17:57,740 --> 00:17:58,350
Look.

302
00:17:59,400 --> 00:17:59,850
These two

303
00:17:59,850 --> 00:18:01,310
are starving like wolves.

304
00:18:02,200 --> 00:18:02,810
Next time,

305
00:18:03,240 --> 00:18:05,240
feed them before sending them over.

306
00:18:05,550 --> 00:18:06,150
Sign here.

307
00:18:10,240 --> 00:18:11,640
I haven't even eaten yet.

308
00:18:14,350 --> 00:18:15,220
This girl.

309
00:18:31,770 --> 00:18:32,900
Eat up.

310
00:18:33,310 --> 00:18:35,000
Tsampa tastes good.

311
00:18:35,440 --> 00:18:36,220
Thank you,

312
00:18:41,420 --> 00:18:42,050
Sir,

313
00:18:42,660 --> 00:18:44,290
are you here looking for Duo Jie?

314
00:18:44,290 --> 00:18:45,660
Yes, I am.

315
00:18:45,770 --> 00:18:47,300
Are you looking for him too?

316
00:18:49,140 --> 00:18:49,660
Sir,

317
00:18:50,500 --> 00:18:52,960
how did you know Duojie would be back today?

318
00:18:53,270 --> 00:18:56,270
I don’t know when Duojie will return.

319
00:18:56,350 --> 00:18:58,350
I come here to wait for him every day.

320
00:19:14,010 --> 00:19:14,870
Duojie is back.

321
00:19:15,160 --> 00:19:18,420
Don't rush. Sit down and wait.

322
00:19:18,940 --> 00:19:21,200
It will take him a while to walk over here.

323
00:19:33,530 --> 00:19:35,090
I’m requesting a transfer

324
00:19:35,610 --> 00:19:36,610
for work reasons.

325
00:19:40,030 --> 00:19:41,090
What work reasons?

326
00:19:41,330 --> 00:19:43,060
I want to go into the mountains.

327
00:19:45,180 --> 00:19:46,440
There will be a chance.

328
00:19:46,790 --> 00:19:48,450
You're brushing me off again.

329
00:19:48,500 --> 00:19:49,050
It’s been a year,

330
00:19:49,050 --> 00:19:50,400
and I still haven’t been allowed into the mountains.

331
00:19:50,400 --> 00:19:51,420
When you picked me

332
00:19:51,510 --> 00:19:52,240
from the Public Security Brigade,

333
00:19:52,240 --> 00:19:53,500
I told you clearly—

334
00:19:54,010 --> 00:19:55,400
since you’re borrowing officers

335
00:19:55,400 --> 00:19:56,010
to guide work

336
00:19:56,010 --> 00:19:56,680
and combat poaching,

337
00:19:56,680 --> 00:19:57,270
I need to

338
00:19:57,380 --> 00:19:58,240
go into the mountains with you,

339
00:19:58,240 --> 00:20:00,140
not just sitting around at the base.

340
00:20:00,140 --> 00:20:01,240
You promised me back then.

341
00:20:01,240 --> 00:20:02,300
But what happened?

342
00:20:02,500 --> 00:20:03,640
You just had me handle logistics

343
00:20:03,640 --> 00:20:04,700
and write reports.

344
00:20:05,110 --> 00:20:05,590
Yes,

345
00:20:06,030 --> 00:20:07,310
you took me to the Qinghai-Tibet Highway

346
00:20:07,310 --> 00:20:08,570
to inspect cars twice.

347
00:20:08,590 --> 00:20:10,550
Does that count as going into the mountains?

348
00:20:10,550 --> 00:20:12,660
And you actually call that valuing me.

349
00:20:12,660 --> 00:20:13,240
Right.

350
00:20:13,750 --> 00:20:14,550
When writing reports,

351
00:20:14,550 --> 00:20:15,350
I'm valued the most.

352
00:20:15,350 --> 00:20:15,770
Those guys

353
00:20:15,770 --> 00:20:17,010
take turns keeping an eye on me,

354
00:20:17,010 --> 00:20:17,740
afraid I’d

355
00:20:17,830 --> 00:20:18,570
write down

356
00:20:18,680 --> 00:20:19,510
their misdeeds

357
00:20:19,510 --> 00:20:20,770
and cause you trouble.

358
00:20:23,900 --> 00:20:24,460
What?

359
00:20:25,400 --> 00:20:25,960
Pen.

360
00:21:14,400 --> 00:21:15,730
Is there anything else?

361
00:21:17,000 --> 00:21:17,740
No.

362
00:21:22,290 --> 00:21:24,020
Say hello to your mother for me.

363
00:21:27,530 --> 00:21:29,160
Why didn’t you try to stop me?

364
00:21:31,110 --> 00:21:32,040
What did you say?

365
00:21:33,590 --> 00:21:34,350
Nothing.

366
00:21:41,660 --> 00:21:42,590
Sorry.

367
00:21:43,070 --> 00:21:44,010
I'm sorry.

368
00:22:14,480 --> 00:22:16,090
Finally, some herdsmen now know

369
00:22:16,090 --> 00:22:16,770
to go to the hospital in time

370
00:22:16,770 --> 00:22:18,420
when a woman is about to give birth.

371
00:22:18,420 --> 00:22:19,350
In the past,

372
00:22:19,460 --> 00:22:20,720
we had to ride horses to the pastures

373
00:22:20,720 --> 00:22:22,250
to help deliver the babies.

374
00:22:22,750 --> 00:22:23,400
Yes.

375
00:22:23,770 --> 00:22:24,270
Now,

376
00:22:24,380 --> 00:22:25,380
more and more people know

377
00:22:25,380 --> 00:22:27,350
to come to the hospital when they’re sick.

378
00:22:27,350 --> 00:22:28,880
It would be great if the hospital

379
00:22:28,880 --> 00:22:29,770
could be expanded.

380
00:22:29,770 --> 00:22:31,330
Patients are living in tents

381
00:22:31,330 --> 00:22:32,680
in the courtyard,

382
00:22:32,770 --> 00:22:34,480
and the sanitary conditions aren’t good.

383
00:22:34,480 --> 00:22:35,010
Ms. Kang.

384
00:22:35,310 --> 00:22:35,840
Ms. Kang.

385
00:22:35,900 --> 00:22:36,510
Thank you.

386
00:22:36,790 --> 00:22:37,120
Here.

387
00:22:37,180 --> 00:22:37,780
Take this.

388
00:22:37,940 --> 00:22:39,050
I have no money left.

389
00:22:39,050 --> 00:22:39,980
There isn’t enough for medical expenses.

390
00:22:39,980 --> 00:22:40,590
You have to take...

391
00:22:40,590 --> 00:22:41,790
You have to take this.

392
00:22:43,070 --> 00:22:45,070
Thank you.

393
00:22:45,350 --> 00:22:45,790
Okay.

394
00:22:48,220 --> 00:22:49,420
I just washed my hands.

395
00:22:49,420 --> 00:22:50,240
It's so big.

396
00:22:52,980 --> 00:22:53,550
Ma'am.

397
00:22:55,090 --> 00:22:55,500
I know

398
00:22:55,590 --> 00:22:57,050
we're short-handed here.

399
00:22:57,740 --> 00:22:58,250
But my parents

400
00:22:58,250 --> 00:22:59,850
want me to go back to the city.

401
00:23:00,200 --> 00:23:00,740
This permanent position

402
00:23:00,740 --> 00:23:01,420
took them a lot of effort

403
00:23:01,420 --> 00:23:02,150
to get for me.

404
00:23:02,180 --> 00:23:02,720
I...

405
00:23:19,480 --> 00:23:20,110
Go.

406
00:23:25,070 --> 00:23:26,070
Thank you, ma'am.

407
00:23:27,740 --> 00:23:29,070
Take this meat with you.

408
00:23:29,070 --> 00:23:29,510
Consider it

409
00:23:29,510 --> 00:23:30,510
your back pay.

410
00:23:31,640 --> 00:23:32,500
No need, ma'am.

411
00:23:32,530 --> 00:23:33,010
You should keep it

412
00:23:33,010 --> 00:23:33,610
and share it with everyone.

413
00:23:33,610 --> 00:23:34,480
Take it.

414
00:23:35,010 --> 00:23:36,700
You haven’t been paid for 3 months.

415
00:23:36,700 --> 00:23:37,460
I know

416
00:23:38,960 --> 00:23:39,810
I shouldn't keep using these things

417
00:23:39,810 --> 00:23:40,850
as compensation.

418
00:23:43,880 --> 00:23:44,500
Go now.

419
00:23:45,480 --> 00:23:50,510
Please drink up.

420
00:23:50,680 --> 00:23:53,440
May everything be safe and sound.

421
00:23:53,590 --> 00:23:58,610
Suoyala, drink in good fortune.

422
00:23:59,220 --> 00:24:03,740
Suoyala, drink in good fortune.

423
00:24:13,590 --> 00:24:15,290
Be careful on the way.

424
00:24:15,380 --> 00:24:16,140
Okay.

425
00:24:27,960 --> 00:24:28,440
Let me.

426
00:24:28,980 --> 00:24:29,500
Let me.

427
00:24:30,200 --> 00:24:30,930
You're back?

428
00:24:32,590 --> 00:24:33,330
I'm back.

429
00:24:33,790 --> 00:24:34,640
Director He,

430
00:24:35,110 --> 00:24:36,090
you're off work?

431
00:24:36,980 --> 00:24:38,050
Mom, I'm off work.

432
00:24:38,140 --> 00:24:39,480
You’ve been gone a long time

433
00:24:39,480 --> 00:24:40,610
this trip.

434
00:24:41,220 --> 00:24:41,900
Yes.

435
00:24:42,380 --> 00:24:43,590
Twelve days, right?

436
00:24:43,940 --> 00:24:45,400
Has it been that long, Mom?

437
00:24:45,850 --> 00:24:47,070
I've been counting.

438
00:24:48,680 --> 00:24:49,220
Mom,

439
00:24:49,590 --> 00:24:50,660
did you use the herbal medicine

440
00:24:50,660 --> 00:24:51,440
I gave you last time?

441
00:24:51,440 --> 00:24:53,240
I drank it.

442
00:24:54,330 --> 00:24:55,050
Mom,

443
00:24:55,570 --> 00:24:57,330
that was supposed to be boiled

444
00:24:57,460 --> 00:24:58,850
and applied warm to your knees.

445
00:24:58,850 --> 00:25:00,010
Why did you drink it?

446
00:25:01,010 --> 00:25:02,350
That would be a waste.

447
00:25:02,460 --> 00:25:03,960
It was all good stuff.

448
00:25:06,700 --> 00:25:08,100
Why didn’t you watch her?

449
00:25:08,330 --> 00:25:09,090
It's fine.

450
00:25:09,220 --> 00:25:10,150
Let her drink it.

451
00:25:10,240 --> 00:25:11,500
It won't make her sick.

452
00:25:12,480 --> 00:25:12,880
Come.

453
00:25:14,790 --> 00:25:15,240
Sit.

454
00:25:21,090 --> 00:25:21,950
Have you eaten?

455
00:25:22,050 --> 00:25:22,590
Not yet.

456
00:25:23,330 --> 00:25:23,990
I'm hungry.

457
00:25:25,570 --> 00:25:32,530
The bright full moon of the 15th day

458
00:25:32,770 --> 00:25:36,720
rises above the eastern hill.

459
00:25:41,750 --> 00:25:42,480
What are you watering it

460
00:25:42,480 --> 00:25:43,660
at this hour?

461
00:25:44,220 --> 00:25:44,550
If you

462
00:25:44,590 --> 00:25:45,880
kill the only tree

463
00:25:45,960 --> 00:25:46,720
in our county,

464
00:25:46,720 --> 00:25:48,400
the County Mayor will come looking for you.

465
00:25:48,400 --> 00:25:48,900
I've watered it

466
00:25:48,900 --> 00:25:50,070
like this many times.

467
00:25:50,070 --> 00:25:51,330
This tree is tough.

468
00:25:51,900 --> 00:25:52,900
Everyone's here?

469
00:25:53,250 --> 00:25:53,740
They bounced along for 3 hours

470
00:25:53,740 --> 00:25:55,480
on the three-wheeled motorcycle.

471
00:25:55,480 --> 00:25:56,010
Mom.

472
00:25:56,440 --> 00:25:57,790
Why are you back so late?

473
00:25:58,220 --> 00:26:00,420
The bank manager made me work overtime.

474
00:26:01,790 --> 00:26:03,650
You only bought three cucumbers?

475
00:26:03,980 --> 00:26:05,240
And they’re so wilted.

476
00:26:05,940 --> 00:26:07,510
I went all over the county.

477
00:26:07,720 --> 00:26:08,050
At this hour,

478
00:26:08,050 --> 00:26:09,310
there’s no leafy greens left.

479
00:26:09,310 --> 00:26:11,110
These were the only 3 cucumbers.

480
00:26:11,590 --> 00:26:12,720
Cucumbers are fine.

481
00:26:13,160 --> 00:26:14,560
Aren't cucumbers green?

482
00:26:15,440 --> 00:26:15,900
Thanks.

483
00:26:16,350 --> 00:26:16,810
Thanks.

484
00:26:16,810 --> 00:26:17,310
Thanks.

485
00:26:17,420 --> 00:26:17,900
Thanks.

486
00:26:18,200 --> 00:26:19,350
Just make do with this today.

487
00:26:19,350 --> 00:26:20,110
Come back tomorrow.

488
00:26:20,110 --> 00:26:21,910
I’ll go buy more early tomorrow.

489
00:26:22,330 --> 00:26:23,250
Your clothes look nice.

490
00:26:23,250 --> 00:26:24,480
Where did you get them?

491
00:26:24,480 --> 00:26:25,740
Pass me the newspaper.

492
00:26:25,940 --> 00:26:27,800
They were brought from the south.

493
00:26:29,220 --> 00:26:29,790
I wish you all

494
00:26:29,790 --> 00:26:31,500
lived in the county.

495
00:26:31,610 --> 00:26:32,140
That way,

496
00:26:32,150 --> 00:26:33,220
you could come to

497
00:26:33,310 --> 00:26:34,200
your Mrs. Zhang’s house every day

498
00:26:34,200 --> 00:26:35,140
to eat and drink,

499
00:26:35,240 --> 00:26:35,880
without having to spend 3 hours

500
00:26:35,880 --> 00:26:37,080
on the road each time.

501
00:26:38,460 --> 00:26:40,320
Living in the county costs money.

502
00:26:40,660 --> 00:26:41,250
Plus,

503
00:26:41,380 --> 00:26:44,240
Meiseng Village is closer to the Uninhabited Zone.

504
00:26:44,640 --> 00:26:45,660
Only 3 hours closer.

505
00:26:45,660 --> 00:26:46,480
Driving into the Uninhabited Zone

506
00:26:46,480 --> 00:26:47,770
still takes a whole day.

507
00:26:47,770 --> 00:26:49,140
The main problem is the county government is too stingy.

508
00:26:49,140 --> 00:26:50,050
Is there enough meat?

509
00:26:50,050 --> 00:26:51,010
We have plenty in our house.

510
00:26:51,010 --> 00:26:51,310
Anyway,

511
00:26:51,310 --> 00:26:52,550
Mrs. Zhang’s hospital

512
00:26:52,550 --> 00:26:53,380
doesn’t pay salaries.

513
00:26:53,380 --> 00:26:54,400
They only pay in meat.

514
00:26:54,400 --> 00:26:55,260
Get out of here.

515
00:26:55,680 --> 00:26:56,790
We can eat meat.

516
00:26:56,920 --> 00:26:58,850
There's one guy here who doesn't eat meat.

517
00:26:58,850 --> 00:27:00,110
I'm fine with noodles.

518
00:27:00,640 --> 00:27:01,610
I just bought some eggs.

519
00:27:01,610 --> 00:27:02,870
I'll poach one for you.

520
00:27:02,980 --> 00:27:03,790
Okay.

521
00:27:03,920 --> 00:27:04,790
Who else wants an egg?

522
00:27:04,790 --> 00:27:05,510
I do.

523
00:27:05,720 --> 00:27:06,770
I want three!

524
00:27:09,400 --> 00:27:10,050
Look at you guys.

525
00:27:10,050 --> 00:27:11,200
You can't even afford eggs.

526
00:27:11,200 --> 00:27:11,660
I wonder

527
00:27:11,660 --> 00:27:12,880
when your development company

528
00:27:12,880 --> 00:27:14,220
will actually open.

529
00:27:15,030 --> 00:27:15,790
Who knows?

530
00:27:16,770 --> 00:27:18,090
During those trips into the mountains,

531
00:27:18,090 --> 00:27:20,290
we didn't do much mineral exploration.

532
00:27:20,480 --> 00:27:21,810
When the company opens,

533
00:27:22,290 --> 00:27:24,480
Duojie will definitely be the chairman.

534
00:27:24,480 --> 00:27:26,740
He Qingyuan will be the general manager.

535
00:27:28,000 --> 00:27:29,800
I’ll just be the deputy manager.

536
00:27:30,980 --> 00:27:33,110
You only did 2 years of primary school.

537
00:27:33,220 --> 00:27:33,680
Have you ever seen

538
00:27:33,680 --> 00:27:35,880
a manager with just two years of school?

539
00:27:36,740 --> 00:27:37,220
Read it.

540
00:27:37,750 --> 00:27:38,250
Okay.

541
00:27:43,680 --> 00:27:45,510
Mrs. Nima's sheep

542
00:27:45,610 --> 00:27:46,700
was missing.

543
00:27:47,400 --> 00:27:49,480
Bai found one,

544
00:27:49,570 --> 00:27:51,720
but she said it wasn't that one.

545
00:27:52,250 --> 00:27:53,380
Alright, alright.

546
00:27:53,480 --> 00:27:54,330
I can do it.

547
00:27:54,440 --> 00:27:55,310
I finished primary school,

548
00:27:55,310 --> 00:27:56,680
and I'm prepping for the Self-taught Examinations.

549
00:27:56,680 --> 00:27:57,720
I’m definitely better than him.

550
00:27:57,720 --> 00:27:58,570
By that logic,

551
00:27:58,680 --> 00:28:00,420
my brother is more educated than you.

552
00:28:00,420 --> 00:28:01,620
High school dropout.

553
00:28:02,680 --> 00:28:03,350
Bai Ji.

554
00:28:03,920 --> 00:28:04,420
Bai Ji.

555
00:28:06,010 --> 00:28:07,400
I found you a new job.

556
00:28:07,500 --> 00:28:08,940
I'm not going to your place.

557
00:28:08,940 --> 00:28:09,720
Your place

558
00:28:09,790 --> 00:28:11,290
can’t even pay salaries.

559
00:28:12,680 --> 00:28:13,180
Ju,

560
00:28:13,500 --> 00:28:15,000
I even went to middle school.

561
00:28:15,000 --> 00:28:15,610
Can I do it?

562
00:28:15,720 --> 00:28:16,420
You can't.

563
00:28:16,500 --> 00:28:17,500
You're too young.

564
00:28:17,900 --> 00:28:18,400
Right.

565
00:28:18,920 --> 00:28:19,660
When the development company

566
00:28:19,660 --> 00:28:20,590
is established,

567
00:28:20,980 --> 00:28:22,640
we won't need police anymore.

568
00:28:22,900 --> 00:28:23,400
Bai,

569
00:28:23,500 --> 00:28:23,790
then you can go back

570
00:28:23,790 --> 00:28:25,440
to your Public Security Bureau.

571
00:28:25,440 --> 00:28:25,920
Right.

572
00:28:27,680 --> 00:28:28,740
That won't happen.

573
00:28:30,880 --> 00:28:32,140
I won’t wait that long.

574
00:28:32,720 --> 00:28:34,180
Duojie has already signed

575
00:28:34,530 --> 00:28:35,990
my transfer application.

576
00:28:39,500 --> 00:28:40,700
When did that happen?

577
00:28:40,720 --> 00:28:41,920
Just this afternoon.

578
00:28:42,220 --> 00:28:43,820
Once I submit it to the bureau

579
00:28:43,850 --> 00:28:45,110
and the Chief signs it,

580
00:28:46,920 --> 00:28:47,220
you won't

581
00:28:47,220 --> 00:28:48,140
see me again.

582
00:28:52,350 --> 00:28:53,310
Of course,

583
00:28:53,440 --> 00:28:54,180
the bureau will definitely

584
00:28:54,180 --> 00:28:55,240
send someone else.

585
00:28:55,810 --> 00:28:56,750
Their reports

586
00:28:57,220 --> 00:28:59,280
will definitely be better than mine.

587
00:29:00,770 --> 00:29:01,830
Are you satisfied?

588
00:29:10,790 --> 00:29:12,120
Actually, everyone...

589
00:29:14,160 --> 00:29:15,400
still likes...

590
00:29:15,510 --> 00:29:16,330
you better.

591
00:29:17,250 --> 00:29:18,590
Yes, we all like you.

592
00:29:27,270 --> 00:29:27,830
Ju,

593
00:29:27,940 --> 00:29:29,400
I... I like you too.

594
00:29:30,070 --> 00:29:31,000
We all like you.

595
00:29:36,380 --> 00:29:37,380
Let me tell you,

596
00:29:38,550 --> 00:29:39,350
it's too late.

597
00:29:39,680 --> 00:29:40,090
From now on,

598
00:29:40,090 --> 00:29:40,790
you can't come to our house

599
00:29:40,790 --> 00:29:42,180
for free food and drink anymore.

600
00:29:42,180 --> 00:29:42,810
Mom,

601
00:29:42,920 --> 00:29:45,380
you'll have some peace and quiet from now on.

602
00:29:48,700 --> 00:29:49,430
Is that true?

603
00:29:51,140 --> 00:29:51,800
Mrs. Zhang,

604
00:29:52,220 --> 00:29:53,500
can we still come over?

605
00:29:56,140 --> 00:29:57,640
She doesn't make the rules in our house.

606
00:29:57,640 --> 00:29:58,720
You know where the key is.

607
00:29:58,720 --> 00:29:59,530
Come anytime.

608
00:30:04,960 --> 00:30:05,400
Here.

609
00:30:07,350 --> 00:30:08,480
This is the last pot.

610
00:30:09,310 --> 00:30:09,970
Eat with us.

611
00:30:09,980 --> 00:30:10,790
I'm not eating.

612
00:30:10,790 --> 00:30:11,940
Dongzhiba. Dongzhiba.

613
00:30:11,940 --> 00:30:12,670
I'm leaving.

614
00:30:13,590 --> 00:30:14,590
Mom, I'm leaving.

615
00:30:14,680 --> 00:30:15,480
Where are you going?

616
00:30:15,480 --> 00:30:15,900
I have things to do.

617
00:30:15,900 --> 00:30:16,900
I'll be away for a couple of days.

618
00:30:16,900 --> 00:30:17,920
Do you have money with you?

619
00:30:17,920 --> 00:30:18,420
You need to carry some cash.

620
00:30:18,420 --> 00:30:18,680
I...

621
00:30:18,750 --> 00:30:19,090
I have some.

622
00:30:19,090 --> 00:30:19,980
I'll give him some.

623
00:30:19,980 --> 00:30:20,920
Don't worry about it.

624
00:30:20,920 --> 00:30:22,120
Wait for your sister!

625
00:30:23,270 --> 00:30:24,000
Bai Ji!

626
00:30:24,090 --> 00:30:25,090
Stop right there!

627
00:30:25,290 --> 00:30:25,850
What?

628
00:30:25,960 --> 00:30:26,680
What are you doing?

629
00:30:26,680 --> 00:30:27,570
You’re out running around all day.

630
00:30:27,570 --> 00:30:28,550
I told you I have things to do.

631
00:30:28,550 --> 00:30:29,380
I'm making money.

632
00:30:29,380 --> 00:30:30,700
You? Making money?

633
00:30:32,030 --> 00:30:32,880
Mom said

634
00:30:33,270 --> 00:30:34,140
you’ve hardly

635
00:30:34,240 --> 00:30:35,180
ever been home lately.

636
00:30:35,180 --> 00:30:37,050
Can’t you let her worry a little less?

637
00:30:37,050 --> 00:30:37,660
Take this.

638
00:30:37,740 --> 00:30:39,200
Don't spend it all at once.

639
00:30:45,940 --> 00:30:47,110
I can make money now.

640
00:30:47,660 --> 00:30:48,120
Take it.

641
00:30:48,440 --> 00:30:49,700
Buy something for Mom.

642
00:30:50,310 --> 00:30:52,110
Where did you get all this money?

643
00:30:54,140 --> 00:30:54,940
Just take it.

644
00:30:55,330 --> 00:30:56,250
I’m about to miss the bus.

645
00:30:56,250 --> 00:30:56,480
I’m leaving.

646
00:30:56,480 --> 00:30:57,140
Where are you going?

647
00:30:57,140 --> 00:30:58,200
Go back inside. Go.

648
00:30:58,570 --> 00:30:59,030
Bye.

649
00:31:38,610 --> 00:31:39,140
Giddyup!

650
00:31:40,030 --> 00:31:40,770
Whoa.

651
00:31:50,680 --> 00:31:51,530
Mom, I'm hungry.

652
00:31:51,530 --> 00:31:52,530
Is dinner ready?

653
00:31:59,400 --> 00:32:00,730
Did you get into a fight?

654
00:32:03,980 --> 00:32:05,040
Did you use a knife?

655
00:32:08,200 --> 00:32:09,260
Did you win or lose?

656
00:32:10,070 --> 00:32:10,770
I won.

657
00:32:15,640 --> 00:32:16,270
Get down.

658
00:32:25,960 --> 00:32:28,220
You mustn't fight with your classmates,

659
00:32:29,240 --> 00:32:30,840
especially not with a knife.

660
00:32:31,550 --> 00:32:32,350
Do you hear me?

661
00:32:33,640 --> 00:32:34,220
Yes.

662
00:32:36,810 --> 00:32:37,900
Go inside and do your homework.

663
00:32:37,900 --> 00:32:39,300
Can I feed Jiongxi first?

664
00:32:41,660 --> 00:32:42,010
Yes.

665
00:32:43,350 --> 00:32:45,700
Come and eat after you finish feeding the horse.

666
00:32:45,700 --> 00:32:46,070
Okay.

667
00:33:14,000 --> 00:33:16,270
Did Duojie really sign it?

668
00:33:17,830 --> 00:33:19,440
He signed it without hesitation.

669
00:33:19,440 --> 00:33:21,170
Didn’t say a single extra word.

670
00:33:22,700 --> 00:33:24,420
You two are so alike.

671
00:33:25,400 --> 00:33:26,440
Both so stubborn.

672
00:33:29,200 --> 00:33:29,810
As long as you

673
00:33:29,810 --> 00:33:31,210
have thought it through.

674
00:33:31,350 --> 00:33:32,280
Director Zhang,

675
00:33:33,140 --> 00:33:33,770
it's just you and me here.

676
00:33:33,770 --> 00:33:35,500
Let’s not beat around the bush.

677
00:33:35,550 --> 00:33:36,770
You sound like

678
00:33:36,850 --> 00:33:38,180
you want me

679
00:33:38,270 --> 00:33:40,000
to stay in the Mountain Patrol.

680
00:33:41,200 --> 00:33:42,090
I just want you

681
00:33:42,220 --> 00:33:44,220
to work with Duojie.

682
00:33:46,140 --> 00:33:47,590
He is a reliable man.

683
00:33:48,050 --> 00:33:49,110
I'll be more at ease

684
00:33:49,200 --> 00:33:50,330
if you work with him.

685
00:33:55,790 --> 00:33:57,790
You're always singing his praises.

686
00:33:58,050 --> 00:33:59,070
I don't feel like

687
00:33:59,180 --> 00:34:00,640
he's reliable at all.

688
00:34:01,510 --> 00:34:02,550
It's been a year,

689
00:34:02,830 --> 00:34:03,680
and every time he talks to me,

690
00:34:03,680 --> 00:34:05,480
it's fewer than five sentences.

691
00:34:05,510 --> 00:34:07,110
He couldn't be colder.

692
00:34:09,010 --> 00:34:10,110
I feel like...

693
00:34:12,150 --> 00:34:13,010
he hates me.

694
00:34:13,590 --> 00:34:15,070
You just don't know him.

695
00:34:15,530 --> 00:34:16,460
Director Zhang!

696
00:34:16,690 --> 00:34:17,320
Bai Ju!

697
00:34:18,500 --> 00:34:19,300
He?

698
00:34:20,380 --> 00:34:21,110
He.

699
00:34:21,550 --> 00:34:22,750
What took you so long?

700
00:34:22,800 --> 00:34:23,659
Have you eaten?

701
00:34:24,130 --> 00:34:24,880
I...

702
00:34:24,980 --> 00:34:27,300
I came to tell them to go back immediately.

703
00:34:27,300 --> 00:34:28,070
Something happened?

704
00:34:28,070 --> 00:34:28,670
Yes!

705
00:34:29,480 --> 00:34:30,170
Wake up!

706
00:34:30,690 --> 00:34:31,380
Wake up!

707
00:34:31,940 --> 00:34:33,000
Get up! Let's move!

708
00:34:36,590 --> 00:34:37,120
Two cars.

709
00:34:37,190 --> 00:34:38,190
They have gunmen.

710
00:34:38,340 --> 00:34:39,440
They went in at sunset.

711
00:34:39,440 --> 00:34:40,260
If we leave now,

712
00:34:40,260 --> 00:34:41,090
we should be able to catch them.

713
00:34:41,090 --> 00:34:41,420
We're exactly

714
00:34:41,420 --> 00:34:42,570
half a day behind them.

715
00:34:42,570 --> 00:34:43,630
Is the information reliable?

716
00:34:43,630 --> 00:34:44,420
It's from the herdsmen.

717
00:34:44,420 --> 00:34:45,280
It's pretty reliable.

718
00:34:45,280 --> 00:34:45,860
Han,

719
00:34:46,610 --> 00:34:47,400
how's the car?

720
00:34:47,400 --> 00:34:48,920
Two of the three steel plates are broken.

721
00:34:48,920 --> 00:34:50,030
We're out of the thick ones.

722
00:34:50,030 --> 00:34:51,190
I put the originals back on.

723
00:34:51,190 --> 00:34:51,840
It gets by.

724
00:34:51,960 --> 00:34:52,420
How long

725
00:34:52,500 --> 00:34:53,460
will the fuel last?

726
00:34:53,460 --> 00:34:54,300
For 2 cars,

727
00:34:54,400 --> 00:34:55,400
it'll last 3 days.

728
00:34:57,260 --> 00:34:57,940
Dongzhiba!

729
00:34:58,550 --> 00:34:59,210
Dongzhiba!

730
00:34:59,780 --> 00:35:00,460
Captain!

731
00:35:08,840 --> 00:35:10,550
Go borrow a car from the animal husbandry station,

732
00:35:10,550 --> 00:35:11,380
buy 300 liters of gasoline,

733
00:35:11,380 --> 00:35:12,380
and get some food.

734
00:35:12,670 --> 00:35:13,600
Tomorrow night,

735
00:35:13,630 --> 00:35:15,230
we'll meet at Zhuoyuan Lake.

736
00:35:15,820 --> 00:35:17,170
The county approved a little funding.

737
00:35:17,170 --> 00:35:18,230
If it's not enough,

738
00:35:20,260 --> 00:35:21,570
figure it out yourself.

739
00:35:21,570 --> 00:35:22,710
Got it. Don't worry.

740
00:35:22,980 --> 00:35:23,840
Leave him a gun.

741
00:35:29,420 --> 00:35:30,480
What are you doing?

742
00:35:30,780 --> 00:35:32,510
You've been transferred away.

743
00:35:33,300 --> 00:35:34,570
Let me go into the mountains,

744
00:35:34,570 --> 00:35:35,570
and I won't leave.

745
00:35:40,320 --> 00:35:40,780
Go back.

746
00:35:43,610 --> 00:35:44,510
Get in the car, now.

747
00:35:44,510 --> 00:35:45,630
Okay.

748
00:35:49,260 --> 00:35:49,730
Bai.

749
00:35:50,280 --> 00:35:51,920
The wind is too strong in the mountains.

750
00:35:51,920 --> 00:35:53,180
You'll get blown away.

751
00:35:54,090 --> 00:35:54,690
Take this.

752
00:36:30,500 --> 00:36:31,690
I'm begging you.

753
00:36:31,800 --> 00:36:33,260
Just give us a little more.

754
00:36:33,550 --> 00:36:35,230
Two hundred liters is too little.

755
00:36:35,230 --> 00:36:36,510
We need at least 300.

756
00:36:36,980 --> 00:36:37,840
How about this.

757
00:36:38,940 --> 00:36:39,440
As for instant noodles,

758
00:36:39,440 --> 00:36:40,900
I'll give you an extra box.

759
00:36:41,480 --> 00:36:42,690
It's on the house.

760
00:36:43,300 --> 00:36:44,480
But I really can't

761
00:36:44,570 --> 00:36:45,670
let you buy gas on credit anymore.

762
00:36:45,670 --> 00:36:46,530
You're already

763
00:36:46,550 --> 00:36:47,750
three months behind.

764
00:36:47,860 --> 00:36:49,590
When we buy gas from the trading company,

765
00:36:49,590 --> 00:36:51,150
they demand cash too.

766
00:36:53,260 --> 00:36:53,840
Wangmu.

767
00:36:54,780 --> 00:36:56,260
Our spark plugs are broken.

768
00:36:56,260 --> 00:36:57,130
Do you have new ones?

769
00:36:57,130 --> 00:36:57,780
No.

770
00:36:58,380 --> 00:36:59,840
They haven't arrived yet.

771
00:37:00,880 --> 00:37:02,070
Do you have any sandpaper?

772
00:37:02,070 --> 00:37:03,030
I have sandpaper.

773
00:37:03,030 --> 00:37:04,160
I'll find it for you.

774
00:37:13,670 --> 00:37:14,670
Fill it up for him.

775
00:37:14,980 --> 00:37:16,170
For the hundred liters of gas,

776
00:37:16,170 --> 00:37:17,500
I'll pay you next month.

777
00:37:23,800 --> 00:37:24,130
Okay.

778
00:37:25,380 --> 00:37:25,710
Do I need to

779
00:37:25,710 --> 00:37:26,630
write you an IOU?

780
00:37:26,630 --> 00:37:27,340
No need.

781
00:37:27,730 --> 00:37:29,460
The gods heard what you said.

782
00:37:31,590 --> 00:37:32,450
Go pump the gas.

783
00:37:36,820 --> 00:37:37,360
Done.

784
00:37:37,730 --> 00:37:38,460
Give it a try.

785
00:37:49,800 --> 00:37:50,730
Sis, it's fixed.

786
00:37:51,280 --> 00:37:51,940
Hop in.

787
00:37:53,510 --> 00:37:55,170
You really have a knack for this.

788
00:37:55,170 --> 00:37:56,500
With skills like yours,

789
00:37:56,670 --> 00:37:57,650
staying in the squad every day

790
00:37:57,650 --> 00:37:58,510
is such a waste.

791
00:38:01,260 --> 00:38:01,670
Here.

792
00:38:04,900 --> 00:38:05,430
Let's go.

793
00:38:06,690 --> 00:38:08,550
It should last through this trip.

794
00:38:08,610 --> 00:38:09,070
But,

795
00:38:09,190 --> 00:38:09,820
it's best to replace it with

796
00:38:09,820 --> 00:38:10,750
a new spark plug.

797
00:38:11,730 --> 00:38:12,190
Okay.

798
00:38:18,500 --> 00:38:18,960
Sis,

799
00:38:19,650 --> 00:38:21,980
do you still want to go into the mountains?

800
00:38:24,570 --> 00:38:25,150
No.

801
00:38:51,840 --> 00:38:53,150
About your transfer,

802
00:38:53,780 --> 00:38:55,500
it's hard for me to give you advice.

803
00:38:55,500 --> 00:38:56,650
You're all grown up.

804
00:38:56,880 --> 00:38:58,540
You can make your own choices.

805
00:38:58,960 --> 00:39:00,560
You can choose your own post.

806
00:39:01,360 --> 00:39:02,820
Whether it's the Mountain Patrol,

807
00:39:02,820 --> 00:39:03,730
the security police,

808
00:39:03,730 --> 00:39:05,840
or the household registration police.

809
00:39:05,840 --> 00:39:06,650
But I don't want you,

810
00:39:06,650 --> 00:39:08,530
just because you feel your current

811
00:39:08,530 --> 00:39:09,660
job is meaningless,

812
00:39:09,820 --> 00:39:11,150
to apply for a transfer.

813
00:39:12,360 --> 00:39:13,960
If you feel it has no meaning,

814
00:39:14,690 --> 00:39:16,280
then go find its meaning.

815
00:39:17,610 --> 00:39:18,500
The reason Dad became

816
00:39:18,500 --> 00:39:19,860
a hero in our hearts

817
00:39:20,710 --> 00:39:22,440
is simply because he was

818
00:39:22,500 --> 00:39:23,900
dedicated to an ordinary job,

819
00:39:23,900 --> 00:39:25,030
just an ordinary person.

820
00:39:25,030 --> 00:39:26,440
An ordinary person who worked

821
00:39:26,440 --> 00:39:28,700
as a local police officer his whole life.

822
00:39:29,010 --> 00:39:29,690
In the end,

823
00:39:30,320 --> 00:39:31,070
no one said

824
00:39:31,150 --> 00:39:32,950
he wasn't a good police officer.

825
00:39:33,650 --> 00:39:35,460
I can't come home for New Year's this year.

826
00:39:35,460 --> 00:39:36,920
I have a training mission.

827
00:39:37,150 --> 00:39:38,680
Take good care of Mom for me.

828
00:39:38,920 --> 00:39:39,780
Sincerely,

829
00:39:40,110 --> 00:39:40,710
Bai Chun.

830
00:39:42,610 --> 00:39:43,340
Sis, look.

831
00:39:43,880 --> 00:39:44,940
Tibetan antelope.

832
00:39:54,860 --> 00:39:55,940
So beautiful.

833
00:39:56,190 --> 00:39:57,130
Now is when the Tibetan antelope

834
00:39:57,130 --> 00:39:58,280
are migrating.

835
00:39:58,920 --> 00:39:59,510
It's also when their wool

836
00:39:59,510 --> 00:40:00,730
is at its very best.

837
00:40:02,480 --> 00:40:04,010
After the breeding season,

838
00:40:04,280 --> 00:40:05,880
there are so many antelopes.

839
00:40:06,690 --> 00:40:07,550
Those poachers

840
00:40:07,550 --> 00:40:08,780
will be on the fixed routes,

841
00:40:08,780 --> 00:40:09,360
waiting.

842
00:40:10,860 --> 00:40:12,460
They kill hundreds at a time.

843
00:40:23,280 --> 00:40:25,010
We'll drive through the night.

844
00:40:25,170 --> 00:40:25,650
tomorrow,

845
00:40:25,650 --> 00:40:27,420
we can make it to Zhuoyuan Lake.

846
00:40:28,190 --> 00:40:29,720
just as the sun is coming up.

847
00:40:30,510 --> 00:40:31,570
The water in that lake

848
00:40:31,570 --> 00:40:33,030
is incredibly beautiful.

849
00:40:34,010 --> 00:40:35,940
I often get up early to see it.

850
00:40:37,940 --> 00:40:38,920
If Duo Jie sees

851
00:40:39,000 --> 00:40:40,260
that you brought me in,

852
00:40:40,690 --> 00:40:42,290
he'll definitely scold you.

853
00:40:43,670 --> 00:40:44,600
Let him scold me.

854
00:40:44,650 --> 00:40:45,730
He's beaten me before.

855
00:40:45,730 --> 00:40:46,420
It's fine.

856
00:40:50,300 --> 00:40:51,210
I've noticed

857
00:40:51,460 --> 00:40:52,800
you all listen to him.

858
00:40:53,190 --> 00:40:53,860
Why?

859
00:40:54,550 --> 00:40:56,010
Don't you think he's good?

860
00:40:58,800 --> 00:40:59,730
He's just so-so.

861
00:41:01,400 --> 00:41:02,440
He is Mazhi County's

862
00:41:02,440 --> 00:41:03,300
big shot.

863
00:41:03,860 --> 00:41:05,090
If I tell my friends

864
00:41:05,190 --> 00:41:07,120
Captain Duo Jie beat or scolded me,

865
00:41:07,210 --> 00:41:08,730
they'd think I'm amazing.

866
00:41:12,000 --> 00:41:12,900
No way.

867
00:41:12,980 --> 00:41:13,590
It's true.

868
00:41:14,280 --> 00:41:15,140
You don't know.

869
00:41:15,710 --> 00:41:16,910
Back in the township,

870
00:41:16,920 --> 00:41:17,780
distributing pastures,

871
00:41:17,780 --> 00:41:18,780
disaster relief,

872
00:41:18,900 --> 00:41:19,820
whatever he said,

873
00:41:19,820 --> 00:41:20,670
all the herdsmen

874
00:41:20,670 --> 00:41:21,600
listened to him.

875
00:41:22,530 --> 00:41:23,510
He's very fair.

876
00:41:26,050 --> 00:41:26,690
In the mountains,

877
00:41:26,690 --> 00:41:28,050
your coat won't work.

878
00:41:28,170 --> 00:41:28,920
Wear this.

879
00:41:44,230 --> 00:41:45,490
It smells a bit, right?

880
00:41:46,480 --> 00:41:47,420
It doesn't smell.

881
00:41:47,420 --> 00:41:48,020
It's warm.

882
00:42:14,860 --> 00:42:15,610
Headache?

883
00:42:16,980 --> 00:42:17,510
A little.

884
00:42:19,090 --> 00:42:20,510
If it's unbearable,

885
00:42:20,900 --> 00:42:21,710
take this.

